
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lintian-info` baraye gereftan etela'at darbareye check-haye Lintian va taghyeer-ati ke anjam midahad be kar miravad. Lintian yek barname ast baraye baresi package-haye Debian va motmaen shodan az inke standard-ha ra ra'ayat mikonand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lintian-info --tags tag_name` --> 🏷️ Etela'at raje' be yek taghyeer khas (tag).
    🔹 `lintian-info --all-tags` --> 📚 List hameye tag-haye mojud va tashrih kutahi az har kodam.
    🔹 `lintian-info --display-profiles` --> ⚙️ Namayesh profile-haye mojud baraye baresi package-ha.
    🔹 `lintian-info --verbose` --> 📢 Etela'at bishtari raje' be har taghyeer namayesh midahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ lintian-info --tags pedantic
    
    🔹 Namayesh etela'at raje' be taghyeer "pedantic".

    $ lintian-info --all-tags | less
    
    🔹 List hameye tag-haye Lintian ba estefade az `less` baraye safhe-bandi.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ lintian-info --tags maintainer-script-uses-dh_make
    
    🔹 Etela'at raje' be taghyeer "maintainer-script-uses-dh_make" ra namayesh midahad ke neshan midahad maintainer script az `dh_make` estefade karde ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lintian-info` command is used to retrieve information about Lintian checks and the tags they generate. Lintian is a tool used to check Debian packages for compliance with standards.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lintian-info --tags tag_name` --> 🏷️ Get information about a specific Lintian tag.
    🔹 `lintian-info --all-tags` --> 📚 List all available Lintian tags with a short description of each.
    🔹 `lintian-info --display-profiles` --> ⚙️ Display available profiles for package checking.
    🔹 `lintian-info --verbose` --> 📢 Show more detailed information about each tag.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ lintian-info --tags pedantic
    
    🔹 Show information about the "pedantic" tag.

    $ lintian-info --all-tags | less
    
    🔹 List all Lintian tags using `less` for pagination.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ lintian-info --tags maintainer-script-uses-dh_make
    
    🔹 Displays information about the "maintainer-script-uses-dh_make" tag, indicating that the maintainer script uses `dh_make`.
